<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RECONDITIONING BRAKE DRUMS AND SHOES - REPLACING LINING/BLOCKS - RIVETING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="5">
        <title>RIVETING</title>
        <para>When riveting linings, start with the center rivets (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0400724">Figure 24</hotlnk>), and use a roll set to upset the rivets. A star set may split
            the tubular end of the rivet and prevent a tight fit.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0400724" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0400724" filename="../figg04/g0400724.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 24. Riveting Linings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The rivet MUST fill the hole in the lining and shoe table (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0400725">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0400725" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400725" filename="../figg04/g0400725.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Rivet Fills the Hole</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The rivet curl MUST completely contact the shoe table. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0400726">Figure 26</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0400726" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400726" filename="../figg04/g0400726.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Rivet Contacts Shoe Table</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the rivet can be moved when checked by hand, it must be replaced (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0400727">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0400727" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400727" filename="../figg04/g0400727.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. If Rivet Moves, Replace It</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If there is more than one open crack in the rivet, it must be replaced (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0400728">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0400728" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400728" filename="../figg04/g0400728.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Replace Rivet if More Than One Crack</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
